{"key":"processedPost-10713945","value":{"id":10713945,"first":10704658,"last":10714353,"when":1248188761,"utime":"07/21/09 06:06 PM","content":"Minimum 4 hours, maximum 24.&nbsp;  I used to soak up to 48 hours sometimes but found a higher bacterial contamination rate from long soaks.&nbsp; Many endospores germinate and form new endospores within a few hours, so long soaks are actually counter-productive.<br />I have a very busy schedule, so don't have time to sit and time the soaks.&nbsp; I usually rinse and begin the soak in the morning, and then PC in the evening of the same day.&nbsp; Often, I'll do the reverse, beginning the soak at bedtime, and PCing in the morning.&nbsp; If I need to run several batches(I have five PCs), I'll go the minimum soak time in order to turn out product faster.<br />RR","title":"Re: Want as many Opinions on Soaking and Simmering Rye as possible."}}